Refactor the Protocol Builder UX so it supports the new adaptive protocol blueprint model.

The protocol is no longer a fixed static pathway.
It is now a clinically configurable blueprint that adapts to:

- age
- sex
- duration
- metabolic profile
- tolerance
- tempo

Do not redesign the visual identity.
Refactor the workflow and inputs so the UX can support adaptive protocol generation.

==================================================
PRIMARY OBJECTIVE
==================================================

Transform the Protocol Builder from a static protocol selector into a clinical protocol configurator.

The user must be able to:

- define a structured patient profile
- select treatment duration
- apply age / sex / duration variants
- review monitoring requirements
- visualize the generated adaptive timeline
- validate and export the final protocol

